==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peripheral
<hw>Pe*riph"er*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to a periphery; constituting a periphery;
peripheric.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>External; away from the center;
on or near the surface; <as>as, the <ex>peripheral</ex> portion of the
nervous system</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Pertaining to minor, unimportant, superficial, or
irrelevant aspects of the matter in question; <as>as,
<ex>peripheral</ex> issues are dealt with in the
appendix</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peripherical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Peripheric</ent>⟦br⟧
